			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~caseih">caseih</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~caseih">( 160668 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64193738"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64193738"><p>KDE on Wayland can still do focus follows mouse, but it is quite buggy, sadly. I'm not sure if this is a problem kwin or the Wayland protocol that makes it hard to do it right.  I'm hoping that when Mate Desktop finally supports Wayland, I'll find a good implementation of focus follows mouse.</p><p>Like you say it's very natural and really speeds up interactions with multiple windows.</p></div>
	</div>

