		<div id="comment_body_64194364">Yes HP-UX was the OS, but I was referring to what was HP's hardware called. I don't remember. Was HP's processor there own was what I wasn't sure about. It had quirks. Unlike SPARC which cut the 4G memory space into heap/stack, the HP did quads. I think the first G was only for code, the second was for shared libraries, third was heap and fourth was stack. I may have it wrong, but one thing I do remember was you effectively got less memory. (Although if I remember right code/shared libs were set as read onl</div>
